   Jul24

:: Texture Details With Woven Pieces ::

   Posted on July 24, 2019 by {tuvalu}
   Standard

What’s Trending Wednesday

   Coastal kitchen and dining area with woven chairs, white pendant lamp
   and striped rug It’s time to get your weave on! Woven furniture and
   accessories are a great way to bring some coastal cottage feels to any
   space. They’re light on the eyes because they don’t have a bulky or
   solid look. We associate the look of rattan with a laid back, cottage
   feel that has the opposite effect of hard lines.

   Woven pieces also bring a nice bit of texture to the space. This adds
   more visual depth while not having to add extra decor. Another big plus
   about woven pieces is that they also come in every shape and size. You
   can get almost anything from a woven rattan chair to the classic woven
   jute basket. You can go wild with woven pieces! Not recommended though,
   you don’t need an entire house filled with woven furniture and
   accessories. Think of them as accent pieces.

   Check out what these designers have done with woven pieces in their
   space! Get inspired and then get your woven goods!
   Coastal details on a neutral color palatte Coastal living room with a
   woven coffee table and beautifully displayed art Modern coastal kitchen
   with natural wood accents and woven pendant lights Coastal bedroom with
   a woven bed frame and blue accents throughout the space

